/**
 * @file analysis.pxd
 * @brief Cython declaration file for the @c analysis C++ class.
 * @details Wraps the @c analysis class (which inherits @c notification) and
 *          exposes its sample/template registration, model training, and
 *          progress-reporting interface.  The Cython wrapper class @c Analysis
 *          owns the underlying C++ @c analysis pointer.
 */

/**
 * @class Analysis
 * @brief Python-level wrapper for the C++ @c analysis pipeline.
 * @details The @c Analysis class is the primary Python interface to AnalysisG.
 *          It owns the underlying @c analysis* pointer and keeps Python-side
 *          references to every registered template and model so they are not
 *          garbage-collected while C++ holds raw pointers to them.
 *
 * **Registration methods:**
 * - `AddSamples(path: str, label: str)` — Register a ROOT file or directory
 *   path together with a sample label used for bookkeeping and matching.
 * - `AddEvent(ev: EventTemplate, label: str)` — Register an EventTemplate
 *   subclass instance and associate it with a sample label.
 * - `AddGraph(g: GraphTemplate, label: str)` — Register a GraphTemplate
 *   subclass instance and associate it with a sample label.
 * - `AddSelection(s: SelectionTemplate)` — Register a SelectionTemplate
 *   subclass instance that applies event-level cuts.
 * - `AddMetric(m: MetricTemplate, model: ModelTemplate)` — Register a
 *   MetricTemplate paired with a model; also sets `PreTagEvents = True`.
 * - `AddModel(model: ModelTemplate, op: OptimizerConfig, run_name: str)` —
 *   Register a model for training with an optimizer configuration and a run
 *   name.
 * - `AddModelInference(model: ModelTemplate, run_name: str = "run_name")` —
 *   Register a model for inference only (no optimizer).
 *
 * **Execution:**
 * - `Start()` — Launch the full analysis pipeline.  Handles meta-data
 *   fetching, graph caching, training, validation, evaluation, and selection
 *   post-processing.
 *
 * **Read-only property (derived):**
 * - `GetMetaData` (MetaLookup) — Returns a @c MetaLookup built from the
 *   cached @c Meta objects collected during `Start()`.
 * - `PreTagEvents` — Set automatically by `AddMetric`; pre-tags events with
 *   model inference before running selections.
 *
 * **I/O settings (read/write):**
 * - `OutputPath` (str, default `'./ProjectName'`) — Directory where all
 *   results (graphs, plots, models) are written.
 * - `GraphCache` (str, default `''`) — Path to the graph cache HDF5 file.
 * - `BuildCache` (bool, default `False`) — If `True`, build/rebuild the
 *   graph HDF5 cache.
 * - `TrainingDataset` (str, default `''`) — Path to an existing HDF5
 *   training dataset (`.h5` appended automatically if missing).
 * - `SumOfWeightsTreeName` (str, default `''`) — Name of the ROOT tree
 *   containing sum-of-weights information.
 * - `FetchMeta` (bool, default `False`) — If `True`, fetch ATLAS dataset
 *   metadata from AMI during `Start()`.
 * - `SaveSelectionToROOT` (bool, default `False`) — Serialise selection
 *   results to a ROOT file alongside the pickle output.
 * - `VarPt` (bytes, default `b'pt'`) — Branch name mapped to transverse
 *   momentum.
 * - `VarEta` (bytes, default `b'eta'`) — Branch name mapped to
 *   pseudorapidity.
 * - `VarPhi` (bytes, default `b'phi'`) — Branch name mapped to azimuthal
 *   angle.
 * - `VarEnergy` (bytes, default `b'energy'`) — Branch name mapped to energy.
 *
 * **ML settings (read/write):**
 * - `Epochs` (int, default `10`) — Number of training epochs.
 * - `kFolds` (int, default `10`) — Total number of cross-validation folds.
 * - `kFold` (list, default `[]`) — Fold indices to run; `[]` means all folds.
 * - `TrainSize` (float, default `50.0`) — Percentage (0–100) of graphs used
 *   for training.  **Not** a 0–1 fraction; `80.0` means 80 % training.
 * - `BatchSize` (int, default `1`) — Mini-batch size for training/evaluation.
 * - `Threads` (int, default `10`) — Inter-operation threads for PyTorch.
 * - `IntraThreads` (int, default `-1`) — Intra-operation threads for PyTorch
 *   (`-1` = use PyTorch default).
 * - `Training` (bool, default `True`) — Enable the training phase.
 * - `Validation` (bool, default `True`) — Enable the validation phase.
 * - `Evaluation` (bool, default `True`) — Enable the evaluation phase.
 * - `ContinueTraining` (bool, default `True`) — Resume from last checkpoint.
 * - `Targets` (list, default `[]`) — Target feature names for GNN training.
 * - `NumExamples` (int, default `3`) — Graph examples logged per epoch.
 *
 * **Plot / debug settings (read/write):**
 * - `nBins` (int, default `400`) — Histogram bins for kinematic auto-plots.
 * - `MaxRange` (int, default `400`) — Upper range for kinematic histograms.
 * - `SetLogY` (bool, default `False`) — Log y-axis for auto-generated plots.
 * - `DebugMode` (bool, default `False`) — Verbose debug output from C++.
 */
